Checklist before moving to Day 5 (Delivery, Notification)


 Adding an item from restaurant A, then trying to add an item from restaurant B, is rejected with a clear error

 Checkout against a PENDING-approval restaurant is rejected; works once APPROVED and isOpen = true

 A COD checkout produces payment_status = PENDING with no payment_transactions row; an ONLINE checkout produces one PENDING row

 POST /api/orders/{id}/payment with status = PAID updates both the transaction and the parent order

 order_status cannot be moved backwards through the update endpoint

 GET /internal/orders/{id} works directly (not through the Gateway) — Delivery Service will Feign-call this on Day 5 to create a delivery record with the right addresses/restaurant


Day 5 (Delivery Service) will be the next consumer of GET /internal/orders/{id}, and will introduce the first bidirectional relationship in the system: Delivery Service reads from Order Service, and Order Service's order_status needs to move to PICKED_UP/DELIVERED in step with the delivery record — worth deciding now whether that's a Feign call from Delivery back into Order, or a status update triggered by the client hitting both APIs. We can plan that explicitly at the start of the Day 5 guide.

